{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, we consider two predictive settings:",
    "(i) Temporal conditioning.",
    "The model G observes an initial trajectory segment of L states u 0:L-1 and must autoregressively forecast future states up until T:",
    "(ii) Generalization from a context trajectory.",
    "In this setting closer to the one of classical numerical solvers, the model observes only the initial state u 0 of the target trajectory, along with a separate context trajectory u 0:L context governed by the same γ, but from a different initial condition."
  ]
}